I'll make you do it.

34
00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:06,460
When I first met you,

35
00:03:08,820 --> 00:03:10,660
I had a strange feeling.

36
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:14,620
I felt

37
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:17,300
scared

38
00:03:18,780 --> 00:03:19,900
and excited.

39
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:27,220
Not only about you

40
00:03:27,860 --> 00:03:29,020
but also your friends.

41
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:31,620
I wanted to avoid you guys.

42
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:35,060
But I also wanted to approach.

43
00:03:36,140 --> 00:03:37,740
I didn't know why.

44
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,740
I tried to get close to your family.

45
00:03:47,380 --> 00:03:48,580
The room on the second floor...

46
00:03:51,260 --> 00:03:52,620
It gave me a feeling of closeness.

47
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:54,700
But it was locked

48
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:55,980
and I couldn't get in.

49
00:03:57,820 --> 00:03:59,020
When you were back this time,

50
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,100
something changed.

51
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:02,420
I felt like a voice

52
00:04:02,420 --> 00:04:04,060
was calling me over.

53
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:06,060
Missy.

54
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:07,620
The second floor.

55
00:04:08,340 --> 00:04:09,260
No.

56
00:04:16,340 --> 00:04:17,940
That day, I didn't know why,

57
00:04:18,820 --> 00:04:19,980
but before I knew it,

58
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:21,580
I was at the door.

59
00:04:27,020 --> 00:04:28,540
I was thinking...

60
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:29,700
About what?

61
00:04:38,340 --> 00:04:39,540
Hanging Mu Dai.

62
00:04:45,020 --> 00:04:45,860
And then?

63
00:04:47,540 --> 00:04:48,340
I'd hang her.

64
00:04:50,020 --> 00:04:50,900
What happened then?

65
00:04:53,340 --> 00:04:54,140
Then...

66
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:56,860
Then I drugged her.

67
00:04:58,580 --> 00:04:59,940
I brought her here.

68
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:14,820
But she was like a different person.

69
00:05:38,260 --> 00:05:39,460
She hit me!

70
00:05:39,780 --> 00:05:41,340
She hit me really hard!

71
00:05:42,580 --> 00:05:43,340
She hit me!

72
00:05:43,340 --> 00:05:43,780
And then?

73
00:05:43,780 --> 00:05:44,540
She hit me.

74
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:46,460
What happened later?

75
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:47,380
Where is she?

76
00:05:47,380 --> 00:05:48,300
Help me!

77
00:05:49,380 --> 00:05:50,540
I can't remember.

78
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:51,460
She hit me.

79
00:05:53,380 --> 00:05:54,780
I think she's telling the truth.

80
00:05:55,140 --> 00:05:56,220
Lady Dai is skilled in martial arts.

81
00:05:56,220 --> 00:05:57,260
I'm sure she's fine.

82
00:05:57,900 --> 00:05:59,220
Maybe she's back home now.

83
00:06:02,980 --> 00:06:03,860
I'll go get her.

84
00:06:10,780 --> 00:06:12,860
Since Luo is in the middle of something,

85
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:16,300
I'll do the recording

86
00:06:16,300 --> 00:06:17,460
for our further reference.

87
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:29,580
Attention.

88
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:31,260
The shadow of water is appearing.

89
00:06:38,380 --> 00:06:39,940
Isn't Bajiao house burned?

90
00:06:40,380 --> 00:06:41,660
How come it's restored?

91
00:06:42,380 --> 00:06:44,380
The burned woman is all right too.

92
00:06:44,580 --> 00:06:46,460
She's even living a happy life.

93
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:50,300
This is what we can see

94
00:06:50,460 --> 00:06:52,140
from this shadow of water.

95
00:06:54,260 --> 00:06:55,340
But it's a little strange.

96
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:58,020
A burned house can be rebuilt.

97
00:06:58,020 --> 00:06:59,660
How could a burned woman recover?

98
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:01,660
This story...

99
00:07:04,260 --> 00:07:05,380
Is it presented in reverse,

100
00:07:05,980 --> 00:07:08,020
starting from the end?

101
00:07:30,020 --> 00:07:30,820
Well...

102
00:07:32,220 --> 00:07:33,260
In your childhood,

103
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:35,700
were you the young savage's friend?

104
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:38,380
She didn't deserve me.

105
00:07:40,980 --> 00:07:42,140
I went to Yueliang Mountain.

106
00:07:42,940 --> 00:07:44,460
She painted a lot in the cave.

107
00:07:45,260 --> 00:07:47,900
About your mother
having fun with you two.

108
00:07:48,460 --> 00:07:49,260
Yes.

109
00:07:50,660 --> 00:07:52,220
In case she was lonely, my mother

110
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:55,140
took me up there to play with her.

111
00:07:57,940 --> 00:07:59,740
Why would a beast be lonely?

112
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:04,060
Did you never play with her there?

113
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:05,420
I did.

114
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:08,900
I played with her happily

115
00:08:09,820 --> 00:08:11,020
and taught her to paint.

116
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,340
You taught her to paint?

117
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:13,300
Or who else did?

118
00:08:14,540 --> 00:08:16,620
If nobody had taught her,

119
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:18,620
how could a beast learn to paint?

120
00:08:19,140 --> 00:08:21,140
Stop calling her beast.

121
00:08:21,140 --> 00:08:22,260
Show some respect, will you?

122
00:08:22,580 --> 00:08:24,140
It's too early to be angry.

123
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,580
When you know what happened later,

124
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:31,940
you'll go mad.

125
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,340
I played with her happily.

126
00:08:36,420 --> 00:08:37,540
Otherwise,

127
00:08:38,580 --> 00:08:40,820
my mother wouldn't have let me
take care of her alone.

128
00:08:41,180 --> 00:08:43,500
And she wouldn't have obeyed me.

129
00:08:44,220 --> 00:08:45,140
What did you do?

130
00:08:48,540 --> 00:08:49,740
Nothing, actually.

131
00:08:52,060 --> 00:08:54,020
I just chewed a mushroom

132
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:57,340
and rolled on the ground,
gripping my stomach.

133
00:08:58,220 --> 00:08:59,300
I frothed at the mouth.

134
00:09:08,660 --> 00:09:09,620
You pretended to be poisoned

135
00:09:10,660 --> 00:09:12,260
and she took you to the village.

136
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:13,780
In the village, I was all right.

137
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:16,580
I shouted and shouted.

138
00:09:17,460 --> 00:09:19,660
I had everybody come out to see her.

139
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:21,420
You should have seen

140
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:23,220
how they hit her with stones.

141
00:09:35,940 --> 00:09:36,820
Shut up!

142
00:09:41,260 --> 00:09:42,140
You know what?

143
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:43,940
She deserved it.

144
00:09:45,180 --> 00:09:46,820
I used to have a happy family.

145
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:51,100
Because of her,

146
00:09:52,980 --> 00:09:53,820
I lost everything.

147
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:56,500
My mother abandoned me.

148
00:10:00,180 --> 00:10:02,020
My father got a new wife.

149
00:10:04,060 --> 00:10:06,220
Do you know what a terrible life I had?

150
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,380
It was all because of that beast.

151
00:10:15,580 --> 00:10:16,540
She deserved it.

152
00:10:57,340 --> 00:10:58,180
Miss Lian,

153
00:11:00,300 --> 00:11:02,380
you never understood their love.

154
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:05,220
You had a loving mother.

155
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:10,540
You also had an honest and kind

156
00:11:11,220 --> 00:11:12,020
sister.

157
00:11:14,740 --> 00:11:16,020
You lost both of them.

158
00:11:17,220 --> 00:11:18,740
But it's not that they abandoned you,

159
00:11:20,980 --> 00:11:22,420
but you didn't deserve them.

160
00:11:23,340 --> 00:11:24,940
All the time,

161
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:27,380
you never deserved.

162
00:11:38,580 --> 00:11:39,300
Well,

163
00:11:40,620 --> 00:11:42,300
you called her beast.

164
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:44,620
But in my eyes,

165
00:11:47,260 --> 00:11:48,460
she's more like a real human.

166
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:31,100
How tragic! That girl was knocked away.

167
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:44,060
Such a miserable car accident.

168
00:12:44,060 --> 00:12:45,140
The police even came.

169
00:12:45,380 --> 00:12:47,500
Look at the tiny pieces of glass.

170
00:12:47,660 --> 00:12:48,460
And the blood.

171
00:12:48,460 --> 00:12:49,220
Yeah.

172
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:51,940
How miserable! Can she survive?

173
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:53,980
I heard

174
00:12:53,980 --> 00:12:55,540
she was a mass of blood.

175
00:12:55,540 --> 00:12:56,340
That's horrible.

176
00:12:56,340 --> 00:12:56,860
Exactly.

177
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:59,340
Her family must be heartbroken.

178
00:13:01,020 --> 00:13:01,820
Look.

179
00:13:01,940 --> 00:13:02,940
Even the car is...

180
00:13:08,380 --> 00:13:10,380
Doctor, come on.

181
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:11,700
My son is injured. Hurry.

182
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:19,980
[Resuscitation Room]

183
00:13:19,980 --> 00:13:20,740
Doctor.

184
00:13:20,740 --> 00:13:21,940
I'm her family. How's she?

185
00:13:21,940 --> 00:13:22,620
You are?

186
00:13:22,620 --> 00:13:23,100
Yes.

187
00:13:24,060 --> 00:13:25,100
She had head trauma.

188
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:26,140
But the CT doesn't show

189
00:13:26,140 --> 00:13:27,180
any bleeding in her brain.

190
00:13:27,380 --> 00:13:28,580
Her condition remains unclear.

191
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:29,820
She'll stay in ICU for observation.

192
00:13:29,820 --> 00:13:30,700
Is she all right?

193
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:31,660
I can't tell now.

194
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:20,400
[Intensive Care Unit]

195
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:35,340
Where's that patient?

196
00:14:35,340 --> 00:14:36,180
Out of the hospital.

197
00:14:37,340 --> 00:14:38,140
Out?

198
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:39,420
She checked out

199
00:14:39,620 --> 00:14:40,660
and left before dawn.

200
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:42,180
Wait a minute.

201
00:14:42,740 --> 00:14:44,060
She left something on the bed.

202
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:55,080
[Thirteen, we're on a long trip.
Take care of the bar. By Mr. Zhang.]

203
00:14:56,140 --> 00:14:56,700
Hello.

204
00:14:57,820 --> 00:14:58,740
Is Mr. Zhang there?

205
00:14:59,060 --> 00:14:59,700
No.

206
00:15:00,220 --> 00:15:01,580
He left me a note,

207
00:15:01,580 --> 00:15:03,700
saying he was on a long trip
with Madam Hong

208
00:15:03,740 --> 00:15:04,900
and that I'd take care of the bar.

209
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:06,980
I called them but they didn't answer.

210
00:15:07,340 --> 00:15:07,860
Fine.

211
00:15:08,060 --> 00:15:09,460
I'll ask Wan Fenghuo instead.

212
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:10,700
Hello?

213
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:12,180
Hello?

214
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:15,760
[Huacheng]

215
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:19,040
[He Ruihua Psychological Clinic]

216
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:33,500
She's up there, right?

217
00:15:40,460 --> 00:15:42,700
Mu Dai can stay here for a few more days

218
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:43,900
for further observation.

219
00:15:44,220 --> 00:15:45,260
Okay. I get it.

220
00:15:53,620 --> 00:15:54,580
Long time no see.

221
00:16:00,780 --> 00:16:02,780
Dr. He is an old friend of mine.

222
00:16:03,140 --> 00:16:03,900
Eight years ago,

223
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:05,500
he worked at Huacheng People's Hospital

224
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:07,100
and dealt with Mu Dai's case.

225
00:16:07,220 --> 00:16:08,060
Eight years ago?

226
00:16:09,620 --> 00:16:10,460
You don't know?

227
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:13,860
How about you tell Mr. Luo

228
00:16:13,860 --> 00:16:16,420
what happened eight years ago?

229
00:16:20,260 --> 00:16:21,900
Eight years ago, Mu Dai was 15.

230
00:16:22,540 --> 00:16:23,340
Back then,

231
00:16:23,820 --> 00:16:25,780
I adopted her
and have raised her for a dozen years.

232
00:16:26,940 --> 00:16:27,980
She was adorable.

233
00:16:28,420 --> 00:16:29,940
She was outgoing too.

234
00:16:32,580 --> 00:16:33,300
Mu Dai.

235
00:16:41,340 --> 00:16:42,060
It's for you.

236
00:16:42,060 --> 00:16:42,740
Thanks.

237
00:16:42,740 --> 00:16:43,260
Let's go.

238
00:16:43,660 --> 00:16:44,940
I was looking for you.

239
00:16:45,220 --> 00:16:46,380
Where are we going?

240
00:16:46,540 --> 00:16:48,740
In her class, she had a close friend

241
00:16:49,060 --> 00:16:50,140
named Shen Wen.

242
00:16:50,460 --> 00:16:51,780
They stuck together

243
00:16:53,140 --> 00:16:54,820
as if they were hand in glove.

244
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:56,660
But later...

245
00:17:00,820 --> 00:17:01,860
Something happened.

246
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:03,780
After school,

247
00:17:03,780 --> 00:17:05,500
they usually went to a tutoring center.

248
00:17:05,820 --> 00:17:08,140
But one night, they didn't come home

249
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:11,020
even when it was eleven.

250
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:12,740
Their phones were disconnected.

251
00:17:13,180 --> 00:17:15,220
We talked to their tutor,

252
00:17:15,380 --> 00:17:17,700
only to know they had skipped class.

253
00:17:18,260 --> 00:17:19,220
Wen's mother and I

254
00:17:19,220 --> 00:17:21,660
looked everywhere street by street.

255
00:17:21,660 --> 00:17:22,420
Wen!

256
00:17:22,420 --> 00:17:23,860
We ended up at an alleyway.

257
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:24,580
Mu Dai!

258
00:17:25,620 --> 00:17:26,540
- Wen!
- Where are they?

259
00:17:36,740 --> 00:17:37,820
It's Mu Dai's phone.

260
00:17:43,940 --> 00:17:44,740
Where are they?

261
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:47,020
Don't worry.

262
00:17:47,020 --> 00:17:48,220
Wen!

263
00:17:50,460 --> 00:17:51,620
Wen!

264
00:17:51,860 --> 00:17:53,740
That was a deserted construction site.

265
00:17:54,580 --> 00:17:55,740
We went in there.

266
00:17:57,620 --> 00:17:58,580
We saw...

267
00:18:00,020 --> 00:18:00,700
Mu Dai

268
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:03,380
had fallen downstairs.

269
00:18:03,820 --> 00:18:05,580
The back of her head was bleeding.

270
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:07,220
Then...

271
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:11,260
We found Wen in the building.

272
00:18:11,820 --> 00:18:12,620
She...?

273
00:18:14,620 --> 00:18:15,380
She was dead.

274
00:18:17,020 --> 00:18:18,660
Mu Dai was in a coma for several days.

275
00:18:20,020 --> 00:18:21,700
When she woke up, she told us the story.

276
00:18:22,780 --> 00:18:23,900
That night,

277
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:27,820
they skipped class for a movie.

278
00:18:29,620 --> 00:18:31,060
But on their way,

279
00:18:32,340 --> 00:18:33,660
they met some rogues.

280
00:18:34,660 --> 00:18:36,260
That's why she had a problem.

281
00:18:38,420 --> 00:18:40,620
Those rogues were caught soon

282
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:41,580
and sentenced.

283
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:43,860
But Shen Wen's parents
lost their daughter.

284
00:18:43,860 --> 00:18:44,900
They had no way

285
00:18:45,140 --> 00:18:46,380
to let the pain out.

286
00:18:47,140 --> 00:18:48,420
So, they blamed everything

287
00:18:49,860 --> 00:18:50,820
on Mu Dai.

288
00:18:51,180 --> 00:18:53,020
Wen was a top student in her class.

289
00:18:53,940 --> 00:18:55,580
She was always obedient.

290
00:18:55,740 --> 00:18:57,100
Her parents insisted

291
00:18:57,700 --> 00:18:59,900
Mu Dai nudged her into skipping class.

292
00:19:00,460 --> 00:19:02,060
If you hadn't taken her out,

293
00:19:02,780 --> 00:19:04,060
